column5: I was down to the creek today and got a few photos of rainbows challenging the fish ladder. If all goes according to plan this ladder will be replaced by a new fish way in time for the Salmon run.
Excellent pictures man! That is good news for m..., that means the suckers will be rolling in soon enough.
Great shots!!!,there determination always amazes me.
Great shots. Driven by instinct. Another example of natures perfection. Thanks for sharing.
Heh heh, the third picture looks like the fish is about to slam right in the wall.
Good fun catching them on camera eh? nice shootin IFH....fish look pretty healthy
They do hit the wall, jump up on the apron and flop around. It's a site.  They jump in and out of the fish ladder until the temp (just a little over 42f) is right and they will be gone in couple hrs.
nice shots. love the colours on them when they're running.
Those are colored up dropbacks! I've only ever seen silver bullets actually making the jump around here. That's awesome!
Always cool to see these pics..
I love seeing these kinds of pictures
